## 3. Sequence Diagrams

Generate **sequence diagrams** for these key flows:

### 3a. Login Flow
```
Actor: User (Browser)
Participants: Frontend (Login Page), AuthContext, API Layer (axios), Backend (auth.js), MySQL DB

1. User enters email + password
2. Frontend calls authApi.login({ email, password })
3. API Layer sends POST /login to Backend
4. Backend checks teachers table (email match)
   - If found: bcrypt.compare password ‚Üí generate accessToken (JWT, 30m) + refreshToken (JWT, 7d)
   - If not found: check students table ‚Üí same flow
5. Backend deletes old refresh tokens for user, inserts new one into refresh_tokens table
6. Backend sends: { accessToken, role, userType } + sets refreshToken in HttpOnly cookie
7. API Layer returns response to AuthContext
8. AuthContext stores token in localStorage, sets user state
9. Frontend redirects based on role: admin‚Üí/admin, student‚Üí/student/dashboard, faculty‚Üí/teacher/dashboard
```

### 3b. Token Refresh Flow
```
1. Axios interceptor detects 401 response
2. Sends POST /login/refresh with refreshToken cookie
3. Backend verifies refresh token (JWT + DB lookup)
4. Generates new accessToken, returns it
5. Axios retries original failed request with new token
```

### 3c. Admin Creates Student
```
1. Admin fills student form on AdminDashboard
2. Frontend sends POST /admin/create_student with student data
3. Backend validates fields, hashes password (bcrypt)
4. BEGIN TRANSACTION
5. INSERT into students table
6. INSERT fee record into student_fees (default 85000)
7. SELECT matching courses by department_id + semester
8. INSERT enrollments for each course
9. COMMIT
10. Return { student_id }
```

### 3d. Faculty Takes Attendance
```
1. Faculty selects course ‚Üí POST /teacher/attendance/session { course_id, session_date }
2. Backend creates attendance_session, returns session_id
3. Faculty view: GET /teacher/attendance/session/:session_id/students
4. Backend returns enrolled active students for that course
5. Faculty marks each student ‚Üí POST /teacher/attendance/submit { session_id, attendance[] }
6. Backend inserts attendance_records (session_id, student_id, status)
```

### 3e. Student Views Dashboard
```
1. Student logs in ‚Üí GET /student/dashboard (with JWT Bearer token)
2. Backend fetches: profile, enrolled subjects, subject-wise attendance, overall attendance, fee record, timetable
3. Returns aggregated dashboard data
4. Frontend renders: ProfileCard, SubjectsCard, AttendanceBarSection, FeeCard, TimetableTable
```

