## 4. Use Case Diagram

Generate a **use case diagram** with three actors and their capabilities:

### Actor: Admin
- View dashboard statistics (total departments, faculty, students, courses)
- **Manage Departments**: Create, Edit
- **Manage Teachers**: Filter, Create, Edit, Delete (blocked if assigned to courses)
- **Manage Students**: Filter, Create, Edit, Delete (cascade: enrollments + fees)
- **Manage Courses**: Filter, Create, Edit, Delete (cascade: timetable + enrollments)
- **Manage Timetable**: View by dept+semester, Create entry, Delete entry
- **Manage Time Slots**: View, Create, Edit, Delete (blocked if used in timetable)
- **Promote Students**: Bulk promote by dept+semester (auto-enroll in next semester courses, create fee record; semester 8 ‚Üí graduate)
- **Mark Student DC** (Discontinued): Updates status, removes current enrollments
- **Re-enroll DC Student**: Reactivate and auto-enroll in semester courses

### Actor: Faculty (Teacher)
- View dashboard (profile, assigned courses, today's timetable, stats)
- View entire timetable (all semesters they teach)
- View course attendance summary (total sessions per course)
- View student-wise attendance detail per course
- View their assigned courses list
- Create attendance session (date-based, per course)
- View eligible students for a session
- Submit attendance (mark present/absent per student)

### Actor: Student
- Login with email + password
- View personal dashboard (profile, subjects, attendance, fees, timetable)
- View subject-wise attendance (per course)
- View overall attendance percentage
- View fee status (total, paid, remaining)
- View class timetable (by department + semester)

